post_text:
REMINDERS!

Online school starts on Monday, August 17th!

The school bus and the van are running their regular routes and times.

Masks are required to meet CDC guidelines.

The school is open from 8 am - 2:30 pm for a ‚ÄúSafe place‚Äù for students to come in (abiding by CDC guidelines) and use the computers for internet, special education services, and tutoring.

Student schedules will be in your new student email accounts by the end of the day Friday, August 14th.

All NEW students have been invited, with their parent/ guardian, to come into the school on either Monday or Tuesday, between 8 am - 2:30 pm, to meet their teachers and get further explanation of our online procedure.

Students are required to check your school email every day, and log in to do work everyday.

Each teacher on your schedule will be contacting you with class directions on your school email!

post_text:
AOBI Graduate Cassandra Pegg:
Day 5. A little update of my deployment to Corpus Christi Texas. I‚Äôm on day 5 of 14 maybe 21 and I am exhausted. Buuutttt it‚Äôs been an experience. I survived Hurricane Hanna, a flood, there has not been A/C at the hospital for 3 days now. It is 90 degrees and 90% humidity. I have worked five 13 hour shifts without a day off, Ive learned SO much about ventilated patients AND covid. This assignment has really taught me so much. I can NOT wait to finish nursing school. Even though it‚Äôs been a tough deployment so far it has been SOOOO worth it and I have learned so much! I‚Äôm grateful for this opportunity and to help people who truly need it‚ù§Ô∏è

post_text:
BREAKING NEWS!
AOBI announces new course!
The most exciting career where opportunities are endless!!!
DRONE PILOT!
Drone pilot is one of the fastest growing technology fields because everyone is using them!!!!
Search and Rescue!
Wildland Fire!
Oil Fields!
Film Industry!
Our own teacher, Glenn Jessen has spent his summer becoming a certified instructor for the FAA Ground School portion for Drone Pilot Certification!!! Our students have the opportunity to fly drones and further their education toward FAA certification.
SO BESIDES OUR NHRA CERTIFIED DRAG RACING PILOT, AOBI WILL ALSO BE STARTING THIS YEAR WORKING ON CERTIFIED DRONE PILOTS!!!!

DEADLINE CLOSED, PLEASE VISIT 4575 S. HWY 95 TO SEE OUR GRADUATES!
Want to honor AND embarrass your 2020 Graduate in one move? Put their face on our super bright awesome LED sign right on the highway in Fort Mohave!
Yes, we're taking submissions to add Mohave County Grads to our sign! For FREE!

How to get their face on our Sign:

Send in an email to mattresslandsocial@gmail.com:
- Class Photo (jpg or png file)
- Name of Student (how you want it displayed, first name works best)
- Name of School/School colors

Deadline: 05-18-2020. MUST send all information to mattresslandsocial@gmail.com to be considered (don't PM through Facebook, sorry). Submissions will be displayed for a week beginning 5-21.

Yes, it's FREE! What are you waiting for???

post_text:
Well tonight would have been the night. We would have spent all day decorating the room. Heather making everything twinkle, and feel like magic. Chris and I would have made a beautiful magic underwater entry complete with a old toppled broken water fountain whispering foggy underwater secrets into the atmosphere, to add to the mystery of dancing late into the night, in the sunken city of Atlantis.
We would have all dressed up in our underwater finery to come to the lost city to crown our king and queen.
I am so sorry we aren‚Äôt there making this memory happen today, but we won‚Äôt give up. We will still have this magical night for every student at AOBI because high school should be a time of memory making! The room is waiting! The decorations are all here, and waiting to to be hung! Even though the invitations that you worked so hard to create say April 3rd? We will know that when we get back together with our Prom invitations, to frolic underwater in our own lost city, that we made it! We made history!

Love Jean

post_text:
It happened so fast;
the world emptied,
and schools followed.

When the nastiness of life rears its ugly head, the problem-solvers will be okay.

They are ready to handle the chaos,
to make decisions,
to try new things.

We've worked with thousands of students, of all types;
we've seen the work you do.

Getting kids prepared,
for when things don‚Äôt go according to plan,
for when they need to change course.

Building the skills and strengths needed in challenging times,
for tomorrow and the day after.

To all educators and students out there...
YOU'VE GOT THIS!

_______

post_text:
Now that most of the students/ parents have made contact with the school, most of you have your gmail accounts ready to go. Thank you!

First instructions:
This coming Monday, March 30th, please come by the school between the hours of 7:30-4, to pick up your students packet. The packet is organized by the student's schedule. Each teacher gathered the student's work and it's all inside.

If you or your student cannot come to the school on Monday to pick up your packet, please email me. Otherwise, we will see you Monday.

NOTE: No one is permitted inside the building. Therefore you'll knock on the front doors, tell Heather or SIerra your students name, you'll sign out a packet of work on the clipboard, and then be given the packet. Inside the packet is a letter from the office and your students work with instructions. There is also a teacher email list for direct teacher/ student contact.

Thanks again for everyone's patience and support.

Hello parents , guardians and students,

Sincerest apologies, we know this is a confusing time. We are working hard to figure out how to do this ourselves, please be patient. We are currently having to switch to Plan B now and we will need your help!

If your student or you currently have a Gmail email they have access to, please send an email to Sierrasowder@aobihs.com using the Gmail email to confirm we have your information correct.

If your student or you do not have a Gmail email currently , please create one for either your student or yourself at gmail.com, there is no cost. This email will be essential for your student's school work and teacher communication. If you need assistance setting up, I am happy to help you and assist over the phone or via email whichever is easiest for you. Please be sure to respond to this via email and update your information with Sierra. Thank you for your patience during this time.

post_text:
Academy of Building Industries High School Staff and Teachers have all completed the life saving Bleeding Control Training, also know as ‚ÄúStop The Bleed‚Äù. This includes but is not limited to wound packing , how to properly apply a tourniquet, and we also installed safety kits in all our classrooms.

A big THANK YOU TO SUNRISE ROTARY CLUB for donating the safety kits for all of our classrooms. We now have the life saving the tools necessary.

ICSAVE , Careflight and Fort Mohave Mesa thank you for taking the time to fully certify our staff through the American College of Surgeons.

If you would like to donate or hear more about this life saving training please check out and SHARE the fundraiser link below to help get kits for all schools in our area! Lets spread the word and #StopTheBleed.

https://www.facebook.com/donate/2796908877019488/?fundraiser_source=external_url

#FlashbackFriday
Earlier this month AOBI's students and staff spent their Saturday at Topock 66 Foundation participating in,Captain Doyle's Rockin' River Clean-up.

Our Science teacher who was the leader of our group said, "It was really inspirational to see everyone coming together to support the environment,and the betterment of our community.We proudly took home the Trash Tracker Award, can't wait to be back at it again next year!"

AOBI students had a chance to meet with Kim Santangelo from the WAVE program today to talk about enrolling in college classes while attending high school including nursing, fire science, law & public safety and many more.

The WAVE Program and MCC have partnered together to help students start their career plans and start their college courses before graduation.

Their next step is to apply and attend parent night on Thursday April 25th.

Mohave Electric Cooperative
January 22, 2019 at 4:30 PM ¬∑

A $5,000 SunWatts Education Grant enabled the Academy of Building Industries in Fort Mohave to complete the School Bus Greenhouse Project last year (unfinished in photo). The students now enjoy a free salad bar with food they have grown themselves. There is just one grant available per year for a school in the MEC service area. It requires a curriculum focused primarily on renewable energy. More about this opportunity will be in the March issue of Currents.
